# Git workflow (logpilot)

Canonical docs: **`AGENTS.md`**, **`docs/agents/INDEX.md`**. Summary:

- **`main`**: release / trusted — **not** for routine coding.
- **`develop`**: **all normal work** — commit **directly on `develop`** (no routine `feature/*` / `fix/*` branches).
- **`experimental/*`**: only for **experimental**, **risky**, or **super major** work — branch from **`develop`**.

Push, merge, PRs, and other remotes: **not** prescribed in-repo—use Cursor or the user.

If the user does not name a branch, assume work is on **`develop`** (directly), not a new branch.

**History:** Prefer **normal commits** on `develop` and **`git merge --no-ff develop`** when updating `main` so integration is explicit and full commit history stays traceable for agents (see **`AGENTS.md`** § History and agent traceability). Avoid squash-only onto `main` unless the user wants it.
